Major OOP Concepts (Very Short)
Class – Blueprint to create objects
Object – Real instance created from class
Encapsulation – Protecting internal data
Abstraction – Showing only necessary details
Inheritance – Child reuses parent features
Polymorphism – Same action, different behavior

Cricket Story – “The Team of Code”
The coach designs a Player template (Class) and creates real players like Virat and Rohit (Objects).
Each player’s fitness and strategy are kept private inside them (Encapsulation), while fans only see runs and wickets on the scoreboard (Abstraction).
A young player inherits basic skills from the senior coach (Inheritance) but bats differently — a bowler bowls, a batsman bats, an all-rounder does both (Polymorphism).

How Story Connects to OOP
Class → Player template
Object → Virat, Rohit
Encapsulation → Fitness & strategy hidden
Abstraction → Scoreboard shows only results
Inheritance → Junior learns from senior
Polymorphism → Different players perform differently